Package cs213.photoalbum.guiview

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MessageDisplay
    Prompts frame to send and receive messages/errors
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddAlbumFrame
    Frame that prompts the user to input the name for a new album that will be added to the user
    AddPhotoFrame
    Frame that prompts the user to input the file name of a photo to add to the current album
    AddTagFrame
    Frame that prompts the user to input a tag type-value pair to add to the specified photo
    AddUserFrame
    Frame that prompts the user to input a username and full name in order to create a new user in the program.
    AdminView
    Frame that holds all information that is visible to the admin user.
    ByDateFrame
    Frame that prompts the user for a start and end date and opens a photoview to display all the photos in the given date range
    ByTagFrame
    Frame that takes multiple tags as input and searches for photos with the given tags
    ListRender
    Creates/Organizes a JList cell that displays the thumbnails and information of photos in an album
    Login
    Creates a Login frame that allows the user to log in with a specified user id or as the admin
    MoveFrame
    Frame that prompts the user to input the album to which they want to move the specified photo
    PhotoList
    List of photos that contains multiple JPanels with thumbnails of pictures and their corresponding information
    PhotoPanel
    Panel that displays the full size image and lists its date, caption and any tags that it contains
    PhotoSketch
    Draws the full sized photo for the PhotoPanel
    PhotoSlideShow
    Opens a slide show that allows the user to flip through all the photos in the album consecutively
    PhotoView
    Displays all the photos present in the album as well as their expanded views and gives the user to edit photo attributes as well as adding and deleting photos
    RecaptionFrame
    Prompts the user to input a new caption for the photo
    RemoveTagFrame
    Allows the user to select which tag(s) to remove from the photo
    RenameAlbumFrame
    Prompts the user to input a new name for the selected album
    SaveFrame
    Prompts the user to rename and save the temporary album created by the search options in AlbumView
    SearchView
    Displays the photos sorted by the given dates/tags and allows the user to save the temporary album that is created with them
    UserView
    Displays all the albums contained in the User and allows the user to rename, add, delete, and open albums or to search for photos by tags or by date
